05,025 were said to have voted for Dim. Then it was a fraudulent election. Stanley Karnow also mentions this in his book , pages 223-224.","$":{"class":"footnote"},"span":[{"$":{"class":"superscript1"},"a":{"_":"6","$":{"class":"_idfootnotelink","href":"00246-AU_Vo_Hiep_txt_split_007.xhtml#footnote-083-backlink"}}},{"$":{"class":"superscript1"}},{"_":"Victory a","$":{"class":"italics1"}},{"_":"ệ","$":{"class":"times-reg"}},{"_":"Vietnam: A History","$":{"class":"italics1"}}]}},{"$":{"id":"footnote-082","class":"_idfootnotes"},"p":{"_":"These bottles contained only dried peppers, cinnamons, garlic, fish sauces, and soybean sauce. But because we were a poor country, we considered those were very valuable. ","$":{"class":"footnote"},"span":[{"$":{"class":"superscript1"},"a":{"_":"7","$":{"class":"_idfootnotelink","href":"00246-AU_Vo_Hiep_txt_split_007.xhtml#footnote-082-backlink"}}},{"$":{"class":"superscript1"}}]}},{"$":{"id":"footnote-081","class":"_idfootnotes"},"p":{"_":"In the book , Neil L. Jamieson wrote in page 162, “In late 1956 and early 1957, Ho Chi Minh himself admitted that ‘errors had been committed’ and urged more moderation and tolerance. A ‘rectification of errors’ campaign was launched, and thousands of political prisoners were released as gesture as government goodwill.” In South Vietnam, we did not know that; they also did not want the people to learn positive news from the North.","$":{"class":"footnote"},"span":[{"$":{"class":"superscript1"},"a":{"_":"8","$":{"class":"_idfootnotelink","href":"00246-AU_Vo_Hiep_txt_split_008.xhtml#footnote-081-backlink"}}},{"$":{"class":"superscript1"}},{"_":"Understanding Vietnam","$":{"class":"italics1"}}]}},{"$":{"id":"footnote-080","class":"_idfootnotes"},"p":{"_":"A sentence from a song that Doris Day sang in the movie , I remembered this because its meaning was very broad.","$":{"class":"footnote"},"span":[{"$":{"class":"superscript1"},"a":{"_":"9","$":{"class":"_idfootnotelink","href":"00246-AU_Vo_Hiep_txt_sp